                  <birth notBefore="1475" notAfter="1485"/>
               <floruit notBefore="1524" notAfter="1527">He was the leading
                  Tǝgrāyān lord of his time, appointed by
                  <persName ref="PRS6229LebnaDe">
                     <roleName type="title">ʾaṣe</roleName> Lǝbna Dǝngǝl</persName>
                  as <persName ref="PRS8158Robel">
                     <roleName type="title">tǝgre makʷannǝn</roleName>
                  </persName>in <date>1524</date>. He was  succeeded by
                  <persName ref="PRS9171TaklaIy">Takla ʾIyasus</persName> in <date>1527</date>.
                  However, even after  having been supplanted as
                ,
                  <persName ref="PRS8158Robel">
                     <roleName type="title">tǝgre makʷannǝn </roleName> Robel</persName> continued to play a leading role in his native
                  province, as a de facto leader of <placeName ref="LOC6569Tegray">Tǝgrāy </placeName>
                  nobles in run-up the battle of
                  <placeName ref="LOC5667Sember">Šǝmbǝrā Kʷǝre</placeName>. </floruit>
               <death when="1529">He was killed in the battle of
                  <placeName ref="LOC5667Sember">Šǝmbǝrā Kʷǝre</placeName> by the Muslim forces in <date>1529</date>.</death>


